# Fix AI Terminal UI Issues - Z-Index and Minimize Button

**Created:** 2025-01-16
**Status:** Planning

## Overview

Fix remaining z-index issue where WeatherMap widget overlays AI Terminal panel, and remove redundant minimize button from AI Terminal header.

## Problem Statement

**Issues:**
1. **Z-Index Still Incorrect:** WeatherMap widget overlays on top of AI Terminal panel when opened
   - Previous fix (tasks/fix-ui-overlapping-issues.md) addressed save indicator and button z-index
   - BUT WeatherMap widget itself still has higher z-index than AI Terminal panel
   - Root cause: WeatherMap widget or its map controls have z-index > 40

2. **Redundant Minimize Button:** AI Terminal has minimize button in header bar
   - Close button (X) already minimizes back to floating button (great UX!)
   - Minimize button serves same function as close button (redundant)
   - Should remove minimize button to simplify UI

**Impact:**
- Poor UX: Map overlays terminal making it unusable
- Cluttered UI: Unnecessary minimize button
- Inconsistent z-index hierarchy

